  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "I've been livin' with devils and angels \n\nAngels, angels \n\nRealize you and I are in the same boat \n\nSame boat, yeah\n\nGiven an integer NNN, for each 1\u2264i\u2264N1\\le i \\le N1\u2264i\u2264N, find the value of:\n\n\u2211j=1N(j\u22121j\u2212\u230aj\u22121i\u230b\u22121)\\large{\\sum_{j = 1}^{N} {j - 1 \\choose j - \\left\\lfloor \\frac{j - 1}{i} \\right\\rfloor - 1}}j=1\u2211N\u200b(j\u2212\u230aij\u22121\u200b\u230b\u22121j\u22121\u200b)Since the answer can be very large, print it modulo 109+710^9 + 7109+7.\n\nNote that (XY){X \\choose Y}(YX\u200b) refers to XXX choose YYY.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first line of input will contain a single integer TTT, denoting the number of test cases.\nEach test case consists of one integer NNN.\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, print NNN space-separated integers, denoting the value of the given equation for 1\u2264i\u2264N1\\le i \\le N1\u2264i\u2264N, modulo 109+710^9 + 7109+7.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u22641051 \\leq T \\leq 10^51\u2264T\u2264105",
      "1\u2264N\u22641061 \\leq N \\leq 10^61\u2264N\u2264106",
      "The sum of NNN over all test cases won't exceed 10610^6106."
    ],
    "inputFormat": "",
    "outputFormat": "",
    "sampleTestCases": [
      {
        "id": "sample_1",
        "input": "5\n1\n2\n3\n5\n7",
        "output": "1\n2 2\n3 4 3\n5 13 10 8 5\n7 43 30 19 16 12 7",
        "explanation": "Explanation:\nFor N=3N = 3N=3, the answer for each iii is:\n\ni=1:(00)+(10)+(20)=3i = 1: {0 \\choose 0} + {1 \\choose 0} + {2 \\choose 0} = 3i=1:(00\u200b)+(01\u200b)+(02\u200b)=3\ni=2:(00)+(11)+(21)=4i = 2: {0 \\choose 0} + {1 \\choose 1} + {2 \\choose 1} = 4i=2:(00\u200b)+(11\u200b)+(12\u200b)=4\ni=3:(00)+(11)+(22)=3i = 3: {0 \\choose 0} + {1 \\choose 1} + {2 \\choose 2} = 3i=3:(00\u200b)+(11\u200b)+(22\u200b)=3"
      }
